{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17476709","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17476709"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:50:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:50:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13932"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13932","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13932"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.21,0.4,0.12,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6551"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50008"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6551"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13932"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35261"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"2616"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13137"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44181"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50008","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/50008"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA seven-year-old girl presents to the Emergency Department with a 30-minute history of sudden onset left-sided chest pain that occurred while she was watching television. She denies any palpitations, shortness of breath, or syncope. Her medical history is unremarkable, but there is a family history of sudden cardiac death. She takes no regular medications and has no known allergies. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Cardiovascular examination reveals no abnormalities. A 12-lead electrocardiogram (ECG) is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the ECG findings?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Normal sinus rhythm","Second-degree atrioventricular block","Sinus arrhythmia","Sinus rhythm with premature atrial contractions","First-degree atrioventricular block"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ECG in this case most likely demonstrates \u003Cstrong\u003Esinus arrhythmia\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a normal finding in children. Sinus arrhythmia is characterised by a variation in heart rate that correlates with the respiratory cycle, with the rate increasing during inspiration and decreasing during expiration. This physiological phenomenon is more pronounced in children and young adults due to their increased vagal tone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal sinus rhythm\u003C/strong\u003E would show a consistent R-R interval without significant variation. While this may be present in children, it is less common than sinus arrhythmia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESinus rhythm with premature atrial contractions\u003C/strong\u003E would show occasional early P waves with a different morphology, followed by a QRS complex. This is not described in the scenario.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFirst-degree atrioventricular block\u003C/strong\u003E would present with a prolonged PR interval (\u0026gt;200 ms) that remains constant. This is not a feature of sinus arrhythmia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecond-degree atrioventricular block\u003C/strong\u003E would show intermittent non-conduction of P waves or progressive prolongation of the PR interval. Neither of these features is consistent with sinus arrhythmia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is important to note that while sinus arrhythmia is a benign finding, the family history of sudden cardiac death in this case warrants further investigation. Additional cardiac testing, such as echocardiography and possibly genetic testing, may be indicated to rule out inherited cardiac conditions that could predispose to sudden death, even if the initial ECG appears benign.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sinus arrhythmia is a normal finding in children, characterised by variation in heart rate with respiration.","A family history of sudden cardiac death warrants thorough investigation, even if the ECG appears benign."],"references":["Ewingdo CC. Wikimedia Commons. Available at: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0","Sauer W. Normal sinus rhythm and sinus arrhythmia. In: Uptodate [online]. 2022; retrieved 2024 Jul 12. Available at: https://www.uptodate.com/contents/normal-sinus-rhythm-and-sinus-arrhythmia","Gajewski KK, Saul JP. Sudden cardiac death in children and adolescents (excluding Sudden Infant Death Syndrome). Ann Pediatr Cardiol. 2010 Jul;3(2):107-12. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3017912/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35261"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13932"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20857"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20857","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20857"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7kJZIr20AB752CYkW6okivBkHneoPy.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7kJZIr20AB752CYkW6okivBkHneoPy.jpg","isProcessed":t